      "message": "Unique leaves has been a requirement of Redfish bmcweb collections since forever.  The problem this patch has overall is that now the rest APIs aren\u0027t generated consistently\n\n/xyz/openbmc_project/my_id -\u003e turns into my_id\n\nbut now if another path gets added, suddenly that resource (that\u0027s supposed to be the same) changes to openbmc_project/my_id, which isn\u0027t how Redfish is supposed to work (see tree stability in the spec).\n\nI understand dbus and Redfish are in conflict here.  If you wanted to have a mode where we just expose the entire path (xyz_openbmc_project_my_id) and add it as a compile mode, that might work, but we shouldn\u0027t be changing resource URIs at runtime.",
